Here's the approach for runtime theme switching in .NET MAUI:

**1. Define themes as `ResourceDictionary` files:**

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Create matching `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with the same keys but different values.

**2. Create a theme service:**

```csharp
public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(string theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDicts.Clear();

        mergedDicts.Add(theme switch
        {
            "Dark" => new Themes.DarkTheme(),
            "HighContrast" => new Themes.HighContrastTheme(),
            _ => new Themes.LightTheme()
        });

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", theme);
    }
}
```

**3. Apply on startup in `App.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    var saved = Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "Light");
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(saved);
}
```

**4. Wire up the settings page:**

```xml
<Picker Title="Theme" SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged">
    <Picker.ItemsSource>
        <x:Array Type="{x:Type x:String}">
            <x:String>Light</x:String>
            <x:String>Dark</x:String>
            <x:String>HighContrast</x:String>
        </x:Array>
    </Picker.ItemsSource>
</Picker>
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    var picker = (Picker)sender;
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(picker.SelectedItem as string);
}
```

**Key points:**
- Use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) in your XAML so controls react to dictionary swaps at runtime.
- Keep resource keys consistent across all three dictionaries.
- `MergedDictionaries.Clear()` + re-add triggers the update immediately app-wide.
